property_value: dcterms:description "The Oral Health and Disease Ontology (OHD) is an OBO Foundry ontology used for representing  oral-health maladies, their diagnosis, and treatment. It is has been used to represent the content of dental practice health records and is intended to be further developed for use in translation medicine. It demonstrates a principled split between billing codes as information entities and what the codes are about, such as dental procedures, materials, and patients." xsd:string
property_value: dcterms:license http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
property_value: dcterms:title "Oral Health and Disease Ontology" xsd:string
property_value: owl:versionInfo "2026-03-16" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000000
name: dental restoration material
def: "A processed material that bears a dental restoration material role." []
is_a: OBI:0000047
relationship: BFO:0000053 OHD:0000191 ! dental restoration material role
relationship: RO:0000087 OHD:0000191 ! dental restoration material role
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000118 "restoration material" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000001
name: amalgam dental restoration material
def: "A metal dental restoration material that consists of alloy that is formed by reacting mercury with silver, copper, tin and sometimes palladium, zinc and other elements to improve handling characteristics and clinical performance." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN: 978-1-4377-2418-9"}
comment: Color depends on which metal is in the alloy at what % (e.g. if copper is more, amalgam become blackish).
is_a: OHD:0000048 ! metal dental restoration material
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6424-4096
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1829-971X
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000002
name: dental procedure
def: "A healthcare encounter that realizes a dental patient role in which the patient undergoes a diagnostic or therapeutic process." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097
is_a: OHD:0008039 ! process during dental visit
intersection_of: BFO:0000015
intersection_of: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000052 ! dental healthcare provider role
intersection_of: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000190 ! dental patient role
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000052 ! dental healthcare provider role
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 5/12/2015:\n\nChanged \"A specific healthcare activity\" to \"A health care encounter in which\"" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/14/14: adapted definition slightly" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000003
name: endodontic procedure
def: "A dental procedure that is performed on the pulp chamber and/or root canal of a tooth, or a part thereof." []
is_a: OHD:0000002 ! dental procedure
relationship: RO:0000057 NCBITaxon:9606
relationship: RO:0000057 UBERON:0001091
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: adapted definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000004
name: tooth restoration procedure
def: "A dental procedure in which either a whole tooth or a part of a tooth is replaced by dental restoration material in order to reestablish the tooth's anatomical and functional form and function." []
is_a: OHD:0000002 ! dental procedure
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000007 ! tooth to be restored role
relationship: OBI:0000417 OBI:0000434
relationship: RO:0000057 UBERON:0001091
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 12/16/2014:\nUpdated definition. \n\nOriginal defintion:\nA dental procedure in which a part of a tooth that has been lost due to disease, trauma or other causes is replaced by dental restoration material in order to reestablish the tooth's anatomical form and function.\nA tooth restoration procedure achieves some tooth restoration objective specification.\n\n1. Added \"either a whole tooth or part of a tooth\", since implants and pontics are also restoration procedures.\n\n2. Removed \"that has been lost due to disease, trauma or other causes\". This is information about why a restoration procedure may be performed, not necessarily what such a procedure is." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan:\nRemoved axiom for tooth restoration procedure that has specified output some \"has_part some  (Tooth and ('has role' some 'tooth to be restored role'))\". \n\nMy reasons for doing this are:\n1) the 'has role' axiom looks wrong. The restoration process realizes the role, but it sounds odd for the process to output the role.\n\n2) Since the tooth restoration process outputs a restored tooth, a restored tooth by definition/axiom has part some (tooth and dental restoration material)." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Mosby's Dental Dictionary 2nd ed" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 3/14/2014: slightly edited definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000005
name: surgical procedure
def: "A series of steps followed in a regular, orderly, definite way, performed by a physician, dentist or surgeon by manual operation." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 3/4/2014: adapted definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Mosby's Dental Dictionary 2nd ed" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000006
name: intracoronal restoration procedure
def: "A tooth restoration procedure in which a dental restoration material is placed into a site that is located in the crown of the tooth.\n" []
is_a: OHD:0000004 ! tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON: Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "filling restoration" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000007
name: tooth to be restored role
def: "A target of material addition role that inheres in a tooth and is realized by a tooth restoration procedure during which the tooth bearing the role is restored to health." []
is_a: OBI:0000444
relationship: BFO:0000052 OHD:0000206 ! functional tooth
relationship: BFO:0000054 OHD:0000004 ! tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000008
name: tooth to be filled role
def: "A tooth to be restored role that is realized by an intracoronal restoration procedure" []
