[Term]
id: OHD:0000133
name: inlay restoration procedure
def: "An intracoronal restoration procedure in which dental restoration material is placed within the grooves and pits of the occlusal surface of a tooth." []
is_a: OHD:0000006 ! intracoronal restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000134
name: onlay restoration procedure
def: "A crown restoration procedure in which the dental restoration material either replaces the cusp or overlays the cusp." []
is_a: OHD:0000033 ! crown restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000135
name: ceramic dental restoration material
def: "A dental restoration material that has a nonmetallic inorganic structure consisting primarily of compounds containing oxygen combined with one or more metallic or semi-metallic elements that are processed at high temperatures, pressed, and polished or milled." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN: 9780323697552"}
is_a: OHD:0000000 ! dental restoration material
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6424-4096

[Term]
id: OHD:0000136
name: titanium dental restoration material
def: "A metal dental restoration material that contains 85% or more titanium." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1"}
is_a: OHD:0000048 ! metal dental restoration material
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000137
