[Term]
id: OHD:0000146
name: noble metal dental restoration material
def: "A metal dental restoration material that is composed of a metallic alloy that contains 25% or more (by weight) of noble metal elements." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1"}
comment: Noble metal elements include Gold, Palladium, Platinum, Rhodium, Ruthenium, Iridium, and Osmium.
is_a: OHD:0000048 ! metal dental restoration material
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000147
name: high noble metal dental restoration material
def: "A noble metal dental restoration material that is composed of a metallic alloy that contains 40% by weight or more of gold and 60% by weight or more noble metal elements." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1"}
is_a: OHD:0000146 ! noble metal dental restoration material
