[Term]
id: OHD:0000191
name: dental restoration material role
def: "A material to be added role that is born by a portion of material and is realized during a process in which the material plays a role in restoring the tooth. Dental restoration material roles are realized in processes that restore teeth." []
is_a: OBI:0000319
relationship: BFO:0000052 BFO:0000040
relationship: BFO:0000054 OHD:0000004 {all_only="true"} ! tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1829-971X
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 12/11/2014:\nChanged definition to read that a \"portion of dental restoration material\" is realized by a \"tooth restoration procedure\"." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 2023-10-17:\nA 'tooth' in the definition may be natural or artificial. Also, the material bearing the role does not necessarily have to become part of the tooth." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 2023-10-17:\nWidened the definition to include other materials used in restoration processes (e.g., luting agents)." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/1/2014: updated definition" xsd:string

