[Term]
id: OHD:0000238
name: extracoronally restored tooth
def: "A coronally restored tooth in which all or part of the natural dental crown is repalced by an artificial crown as a result of the tooth undergoing an crown procedure." []
is_a: OHD:0000237 ! coronally restored tooth
