[Term]
id: OHD:0000261
name: tooth abfraction lesion
def: "A mechanical tooth lesion formed as a result of the tooth being fatigued, flexed, and deformed by biomechanical loading of the tooth. Tooth abfactions are primarily found in the cervical region of the tooth." [] {IAO:0000119="SNOMED CT \"Abfraction (disorder)\" (SCTID: 109750005)"}
