[Term]
id: OHD:0000289
name: pulpal regeneration procedure
def: "A surgical endodontic procedure during which medications are placed inside the pulp chamber in order to induce the formation of living replacement tissue." []
is_a: OHD:0000243 ! surgical endodontic procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://www.neendosol.com/procedures/pulpal-regeneration/" xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:34:17Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000290
name: tooth friction lesion
def: "A mechnical tooth lesion that formed as a result of some friction process." []
is_a: OHD:0000271 ! mechanical tooth lesion
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0006-7251-3026
property_value: dcterms:created "2023-06-22T21:30:59Z" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "A tooth friction lesion is caused by a friction process involving an external object. For example, the clasp of an ill-fitting denture, pipe stem of a tobacco pipe, friction lesion of the interproximal areas caused by vigorous use of a tooth pick etc. An abrasive material is not involved in creating the friction lesion." xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000291
name: removable maxillary partial denture procedure
def: "A removable partial denture procedure in which the prosthesis being constructed or fitted replaces some but not all of the patient's maxillary teeth." []
is_a: OHD:0000250 ! removable partial denture procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
creation_date: 2022-12-06T04:15:55Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000292
name: removable mandibular partial denture procedure
