[Term]
id: OHD:0000444
name: Modified Dental Anxiety Scale (MDAS)
def: "A dental fear and anxiety assessment instrument initially described by Humphris et al. (1995) that was developed to improve the psychometrics and content validity of the original Dental Anxiety Scale (DAS) by adding an item about receiving dental injections, and ordering the potential answers to each item so that they range from least to greatest level of anxiety." [] {IAO:0000119="https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1186/1472-6831-8-29.pdf", IAO:0000119="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/1472-6831-9-20"}
def: "A dental fear survey consisting of five questions and summed together to produce a total score ranging from 5 to 25." [] {IAO:0000119="Humphris, G., T. Morrison, and S. J. E. Lindsay. \"The Modified Dental Anxiety Scale: UK norms and evidence for validity.\" Community Dental Health 12.3 (1995): 143-150.", IAO:0000119="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/1472-6831-9-20"}
subset: OHD:0005009
is_a: OHD:0008008 ! dental fear and anxiety assessment instrument
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0002-7282-0836
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-02-15T19:01:50Z" xsd:dateTime

