[Term]
id: OHD:0008017
name: Index of Dental Anxiety and Fear (IDAF-4C+)
def: "A dental assessment instrument developed by Armfield (2010) to measure the four components of anxiety (emotional, behavioural, physiological, cognitive), which provides a screening measure for the psychiatric anxiety diagnosis of specific phobia of dentistry, and which comprises common dental anxiety triggers relevant to both clinicians and research." [] {IAO:0000119="https://psycnet.apa.org/buy/2010-10892-008", IAO:0000119="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/eos.12731"}
