[Term]
id: OHD:0008051
name: nausea
comment: We're not using the symptom ontology 'nausea' class, since this makes nausea a type of symptom, and this doesn't give a good way of stating what it's a symptom of. We prefer to use a 'symptom of' relation. We also don't like the definition they give of symptom, since symptoms are not necessarily perceived or reported.
