[Term]
id: OHD:0010232
name: secondary myofascial orofacial pain
def: "Myofascial pain caused by an underlying disorder (inflammation, infection or muscle spasm)." []
comment: ICOP number: 2.2
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010003 ! myofascial orofacial pain
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:44:16Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010233
name: myofascial orofacial pain attributed to tendonitis
def: "Pain of tendon origin, affected by jaw movement, function or parafunction and replicated by provocation-testing of the relevant masticatory tendon. Limitation of mandibular movement(s) secondary to pain may be present. The temporalis tendon is a common site of tendonitis and may refer pain to the teeth and other nearby structures. Tendonitis can also occur in other masticatory muscle tendons." []
comment: ICOP number: 2.2.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010232 ! secondary myofascial orofacial pain
relationship: RO:0002410 OHD:0010291 ! tendonitis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:46:19Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010234
name: myofascial orofacial pain attributed to myositis
def: "Pain caused by myositis affecting one or more masticatory muscles, with clinical characteristics of inﬂammation or infection: oedema, erythema and/or increased temperature. It generally arises acutely following direct trauma of the muscle or from infection, or chronically with autoimmune disease. Limitation of unassisted mandibular movements secondary to pain is often present. Calciﬁcation of the muscle can occur (i.e. myositis ossiﬁcans)." []
comment: ICOP number: 2.2.2
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010232 ! secondary myofascial orofacial pain
relationship: RO:0002410 OHD:0010305 ! myositis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:48:14Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010235
name: myofascial orofacial pain attributed to muscle spasm
def: "Pain caused by sudden, involuntary, reversible tonic contraction of a muscle. Such spasm may affect any of the masticatory muscles. Acute malocclusion may be present." []
comment: ICOP number: 2.2.3
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010232 ! secondary myofascial orofacial pain
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:49:34Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010236
name: temporomandibular joint pain attributed to arthritis
def: "TMJ pain caused by persistent inflammation of articular tissues (due, for example, to trauma, infection, crystal deposition or autoimmune disorder). TMJ pain is common in TMJ arthritis, but TMJ arthritis can be present without pain." []
comment: ICOP number: 3.2.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010128 ! secondary temporomandibular joint pain
relationship: RO:0002410 OHD:0010306 ! inflammatory arthritis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:52:37Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010237
name: temporomandibular joint pain attributed to non-systemic arthritis
def: "Temporomandibular joint pain due to arthritis with evidence of systemic inflammatory joint disease but not evidence that associates it with the TMJ pain or no evidence of rheumatological disease." []
comment: ICOP number: 3.2.1.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010236 ! temporomandibular joint pain attributed to arthritis
relationship: RO:0002410 OHD:0010307 ! non-systemic inflammatory arthritis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:53:36Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010238
name: temporomandibular joint pain attributed to systemic arthritis
def: "Temporomandibular joint due to arthritis with evidence of systemic inflammatory joint disease, pain developed in close temporal relation to other symptoms, and either the pain has significantly worsened in parallel with worsening of the systemic inflammatory joint disease or the pain has significantly improved or resolved with treatment of the systemic inflammatory joint disease." []
comment: ICOP number: 3.2.1.2
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010236 ! temporomandibular joint pain attributed to arthritis
relationship: RO:0002410 OHD:0010308 ! systemic inflammatory arthritis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-01T17:54:43Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010239
name: temporomandibular joint pain attributed to disc displacement
def: "TMJ pain caused by TMJ disc displacement in the absence of TMJ arthritis. TMJ pain can here be due to mechanical derangements within the joint." []
