[Term]
id: OHD:0010259
name: tension-type orofacial pain
def: "Episodic or chronic pain exclusively in the orofacial region, without head pain, with the characteristics and associated features of 2. Tension-type headache described in the International Classification of Headache Disorders 3rd Edition, which can include pressing or tightening with mild to moderate intensity with bilateral location." []
comment: ICOP number: 5.2
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010255 ! orofacial pain with headache presentation
