[Term]
id: OHD:0010268
name: short-lasting unilateral neuralgiform facial pain attacks with cranial autonomic symptoms (SUNFA)
def: "Attacks of moderate or severe, strictly unilateral oral and/or facial pain, without head pain, lasting seconds to minutes, occurring at least once a day and usually associated with prominent lacrimation and redness of the ipsilateral eye and/or other local autonomic symptoms and/or signs." []
