[Term]
id: OHD:0010275
name: idiopathic orofacial pain
def: "Orofacial pain involving unilateral or bilateral intraoral or facial pain in the distribution(s) of one or more branches of the trigeminal nerve(s) for which the aetiology is unknown. The pain is usually persistent, of moderate intensity, poorly localized and described as dull, pressing or of burning character." []
comment: ICOP number: 6
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010000 ! orofacial pain
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-07T17:31:21Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010276
name: burning mouth syndrome (BMS)
def: "An intraoral burning or dysaesthetic sensation, recurring daily for more than 2 hours per day for more than 3 months, without evident causative lesions on clinical examination and investigation." []
comment: ICOP number: 6.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010275 ! idiopathic orofacial pain
