[Term]
id: OHD:0010278
name: burning mouth syndrome with somatosensory changes
def: "An intraoral burning or dysaesthetic sensation, recurring daily for more than 2 hours per day for more than 3 months and accompanied by negative and/or positive somatosensory changes, without evident causative lesion(s) on clinical examination and investigation." []
comment: ICOP number: 6.1.2
