[Term]
id: OHD:0010280
name: persistent idiopathic facial pain (PIFP)
def: "Persistent facial pain, with variable features, recurring daily for more than 2 hours per day for more than 3 months, in the absence of clinical neurological deficit or preceding causative event." []
