[Term]
id: OHD:0010301
name: trigeminal postherpetic neuralgia
def: "Unilateral facial pain persisting or recurring for at least 3 months in the distribution(s) of one or more branches of the trigeminal nerve, with variable sensory changes, caused by herpes zoster." []
