[Term]
id: OHD:0010302
name: post-traumatic trigeminal neuropathic pain
def: "Unilateral or bilateral facial or oral pain following and caused by trauma to the trigeminal nerve(s), with other symptoms and/or clinical signs of trigeminal nerve dysfunction, and persisting or recurring for more than 3 months." []
