[Typedef]
id: OHD:0000091
name: is dental restoration of
def: "This relation holds between some restorative material and some part of a tooth in which the restorative material restores or replaces lost tooth structure, oral tissues, tooth (structural) integrity, or tooth functioning." []
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Bill Duncan 6/27/2012:\nThis relation is intended to capture the relationship between restorative materials, such as amalagam, and the tooth (or teeth) that is being repaired.  Some examples in which this relation obtains include fillings, crowns, bridges, and inlays. \n\nIt is going to be a shortcut relation between the material, the tooth in which the material is located, and the site formed for the restoration (e.g., a hole formed by drilling).  The details of this still need to be worked out." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Titus Schleyer 1/1/2014: nice definition!" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON: Bill Duncan" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Adapted from:\nMosby's Dental Dictionary, 2nd Edition. page 580. \nWikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dental_restoration" xsd:string

[Typedef]
id: OHD:0000216
name: next visit
def: "relates a health care encounter such as a inpatient, outpatient, or hospital stay to the next such encounter for the same patient." []
property_value: IAO:0000116 "precedes is too general as it doesn't have any constraint on continuity of participants. However it is the case a visit precedes the next one." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "relation added as a convenience for survival analysis queries." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
is_a: OHD:0000217 ! later visit

